  "why": "The paper proposes NLC and evaluates it across many models and tasks, but it contains no design elements intended to discover transferable faults (e.g., surrogate-model feedback or cross-model guidance) and presents no experiments that reuse fault-inducing inputs found on one model to test other, unseen models. All fuzzing/adversarial experiments and coverage-guided mutations are performed and measured per-target model (AEs and fuzzing seeds are created and evaluated for the same model), so the paper does not demonstrate cross-model attack transferability.",
